<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-27T14:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-27T14:36:00-05:00" n="882" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d882">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6412.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-27T13:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 27, 1913—1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>52. Zapata, Salazar, Argumedo and all rebel chiefs in Vera Cruz and Nuevo
                            Laredo have submitted to the Provisional Government. Orozco has
                            announced his adherence. Difficulties still exist in the States of
                            Coahuila, Sonora, Chihuahua and Durango.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>